The observer pattern is a software design pattern in which an object, called the subject, maintains a list of its dependents, called observers,
and notifies them automatically of any state changes, usually by calling one of their methods.

example
- weather station - weatherData need to notify different weather display
- cricket app that notifies viewers about the information such as current score, run rate etc.
- a news agency can notify channels when it receives news.
- subscribe magzine/newspaper


